visual_content: A green box with a graphic of an electric car and a charging plug. Text reads '10%' and 'SAVE MONEY ON CHARGING'.

A green graphic showing an EV charging at a station, with text '10% off EV charging' and 'Gojek driver-partners enjoy upfront EV charging discounts!' The graphic also displays logos for 'Gojek' and 'CD ENGIC'. Below this, there are input fields for 'Mobile/UPI ID' and 'Charge Amount (Points)', and a 'Start Charging' button.

A promotional image with the text 'ElectroCharge' and 'UNLOCK HUGE SAVINGS GET 30% OFF ALL CHARGES THIS MONTH'. It features an image of an electric car and a charging station. Below this, the text 'CHARGE30 APPLY NOW' is displayed.
anomalies: The discount of '30% OFF' combined with the generic savings message and the call to action 'APPLY NOW' could be indicative of a phishing attempt or a social engineering tactic to lure users into providing personal information or clicking a malicious link if this were a real-time interface. However, based solely on the visual, it's a standard promotion format. No clear signs of deepfake or AI-generated images are present.
